re is a consensus of thought across the political spectrum underpinned by the contemporary acceptance of the impossibility of human emancipation. Ultimately, Race Defaced is a heretical intervention into questions of race and racism that challenges both conservative and radical orthodoxies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAnti-racismzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aAnti-racismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aCapitalismxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aCapitalismxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRacismzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aRacismzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh1 aKyriakides, Christopher, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478315640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804783156423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804783156.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles